  "texts": [
    "Through engagement with the toxic material, moderators may be deemed victims as well.",
    "Despite low pay and little training, however, we can imagine that some will martial on, becoming frontline \"educators,\" \"legislators,\" and \"judges\" of what is tolerable or obscene.",
    "Their job is not only morally fraught but also organizationally complex (in-house, to maintain control, or outsourced, due to lower costs, lighter regulation, or language and cultural expertise?).",
    "A sense of community and social support among fellow workers is necessary to survive (similarly with Mumbai ragpickers, as described by Shepherd et al. [2022]).",
    "Among those who began exclusively for the income, perhaps some will remain, having developed a sense of purpose and mission: to protect those even more vulnerable and to set a moral tone for society."
